    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are positioned for a high-ceiling offensive output today, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** (80.30) and **Junior Caminero** (76.17). **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a massive 19% SP skill adjustment facing Hancock, while **Junior Caminero** capitalizes on the highest opposing xERA (5.74) of the day, effectively neutralizing his park factor penalty. **Christian Yelich** (75.84) rounds out our elite tier, boosted by a favorable 13% dynamic platoon edge against Irvin. While **Hyeseong Kim** carries a lower score (56.79), he remains an intriguing play; his 4% efficiency bump for the \"Slow SP Delivery\" factor makes him a targeted SB acquisition against Rocker, despite the suboptimal 9th-spot placement.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today involved **Josh Smith**, who sits on our bench with a 49.58 score. He was the most viable alternative, buoyed by a 14% dynamic platoon advantage against Glasnow; however, the optimizer favored **Dillon Dingler** (49.94) and **Chase Meidroth** (51.80) due to their higher batting order stability and more favorable matchups against pitchers with higher xERA profiles. Meanwhile, we continue to exercise caution with **Victor Scott II** (34.48) and **Logan O'Hoppe** (33.27), both of whom fell well below our 40.0 efficiency floor; their struggles against elite arms like Early and Burns, coupled with unfavorable platoon matchups, mandate they stay benched to protect our limited game caps. \n\nManagers should keep a close watch on **Trea Turner** (63.69) and **Kyle Schwarber** (60.47) as they face the deceptive skill of Soroka; while their raw scores are robust, the 5% SP skill penalty serves as a reminder that elite arms can stifle high-floor contributors. We remain bullish on **Colt Keith** (68.51) and **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (66.90), as both players leverage strong platoon adjustments to maintain their \"Strong\" classification. We are avoiding exposure to **Carson Benge** today as his 41.57 rating sits dangerously close to the floor, providing little statistical justification to deploy him over our current starting core.",
